body.raw:
## What is Markdown?

Markdown is a way to style text on the web. You control the display of the document; formatting words as bold or italic, adding images, and creating lists are just a few of the things we can do with Markdown. Mostly, Markdown is just regular text with a few non-alphabetic characters thrown in, like `#` or `*`.

## Syntax guide

Here’s an overview of Markdown syntax that you can use anywhere on GitHub.com or in your own text files.

### Headings

```txt
## This is a h2 tag

### This is a h3 tag

#### This is a h4 tag
```

## This is a h2 tag

### This is a h3 tag

#### This is a h4 tag

:::info
h2 should be the top-level heading instead of h1 which is for the title.
:::

### Emphasis

```txt
_This text will be italic_

**This text will be bold**

_You **can** combine them_
```

_This text will be italic_

**This text will be bold**

_You **can** combine them_

### Strikethrough

Any word wrapped with two tildes (like `~~this~~`) will appear ~~crossed out~~.

### Lists

#### Unordered

```txt
- Item 1
- Item 2
  - Item 2a
  - Item 2b
```

- Item 1
- Item 2
  - Item 2a
  - Item 2b

#### Ordered

```txt
1. Item 1
1. Item 2
1. Item 3
   1. Item 3a
   1. Item 3b
```

1. Item 1
1. Item 2
1. Item 3
   1. Item 3a
   1. Item 3b

### Images

```txt
![Office](/images/office-chairs.webp)
```

![Office](/images/office-chairs.webp)

### Links

```txt
http://github.com

[GitHub](http://github.com)
```

http://github.com

[GitHub](http://github.com)

### Blockquotes

```txt
As Kanye West said:

> We're living the future so
> the present is our past.
```

As Kanye West said:

> We're living the future so
> the present is our past.

### Inline code

```txt
I think you should use an `<addr>` element here instead.
```

I think you should use an `<addr>` element here instead.

### Syntax highlighting

Here’s an example of how you can use syntax highlighting with [GitHub Flavored Markdown](https://help.github.com/articles/basic-writing-and-formatting-syntax/):

````txt
```js title="/lib/sum.js"
// Some comments
function sum(x, y) {
  return x + y;
}
```
````

And here's how it looks - nicely colored with styled code titles!

```js title="/lib/sum.js"
// Some comments
function sum(x, y) {
  return x + y;
}
```

### Messages

```txt
:::info
You can use **Markdown** inside `Message`.
:::

:::warn
You can use **Markdown** inside `Message`.
:::

:::danger
You can use **Markdown** inside `Message`.
:::
```

:::info
You can use **Markdown** inside `Message`.
:::

:::warn
You can use **Markdown** inside `Message`.
:::

:::danger
You can use **Markdown** inside `Message`.
:::

### Tables

You can create tables by assembling a list of words and dividing them with hyphens `-` (for the first row), and then separating each column with a pipe `|`:

```txt
| First Header                | Second Header                |
| --------------------------- | ---------------------------- |
| Content from cell 1         | Content from cell 2          |
| Content in the first column | Content in the second column |
```

| First Header                | Second Header                |
| --------------------------- | ---------------------------- |
| Content from cell 1         | Content from cell 2          |
| Content in the first column | Content in the second column |

body.raw:
## At artus

Lorem markdownum gentes; vel hanc murmur carinam gerentem adspicio. Sacro adit
**fibula ad ut** non [parentis veniebat](https://example.com)
invidiosior tecta, nam pallent Phaethon cum erit nec. Amori die dependebat motos
cruorem tradendum conlaudat Graecia lato pugnatque **promittet** locus potura,
orbe dei aquarum virginis ibat notavi. Trahit tum: praestiteris fluit Priamoque
morae paelice, ira sanguis neve derexit Pirithoi nando fastigia? Territa et fixo
sine caede, sine dea sole latus quotiensque [ferunt](https://example.com)
mutat?

Tendebat sis quippe et excussaque: inquit [nunc leto
ter](https://example.com), in vulnere facta nunc sanguine, sive tura
dicens. Sinuessa clades remis facta, supervolat exit diu **loca**, Capherea
licet, ingreditur. Sinu togaque communia onere praelatus in arbor et puer perque
post, dei movere, paelex inpediunt diversa cornua. Cortice potest! _Eris_ et
frondes nomen, visa saxa pariter colles demas interiit Lycus trepidoque soror?

Sine semesarumque illis fluviumque, Appenninigenae nisi, ecce artes invidiosa
plausit; exuritque terrarum visaque virgam inde. Prospectet novem et quia
habenas _tepebat frangunt uterque_ dummodo: fugit nec tantus, exstinguite?
Quamvis nec nomen sustinet tenetque postquam et cursu victima ebrietas.

## Potes terrent ostendi quotiens addit capellae socerum

Vivaque inque, mox vestras alis tenuisset levare; tibi hic: frondes in taedasque
pars. Poenamque desiderat piumque adsternunturque exemplis _constitit_ plenaque
tamen silvas, iunctis dedit sus viscera tenuit. Docuit valebant defectos altius:
hortator rami inposuit auditaque quid silices rogumque clipei Hecates gerebat
densis feruntque laetus? Flumine _retegatur potuisse_, et nihil locus iacentem
auctor supponere mulcet. Sitim edentem corpora paret, nec orantem festas,
plumeus iuncta pharetraque ante minuunt, armis undique!

> Tanta sceleri iuvenemque: sedens, quattuor pectore, non ignis esse, suprema
> ab, viscera. Oriente et flecti fertur si. Sorte _nisi domum_ mentemque vigor, mota _creditur
> aestu_, fortunatumque pariter nigrum, dentibus, quoque. Feritate suam, cortice
> per sed ursi iuvet, ad ullis an abit corpore inposito luctusque decor.
> Ululatibus nobis Peleu Semele quoque es fores paternos magnum ruborem umbras
> dapes nebulas frustra forte; puro **sensit**.

Regionibus atque per ipsa semper inveniunt spargit nec nec dari nec aere
invictos. Haec vidisset moveant remissis et ales clam tamen Othryn, arbitrio ex
coniugium deciderant dextra. **Cum et** vident quoque cornua flumina invenit
amando: postquam vana.

Admiserat velatus inpedienda canes facilesque effugit dum [in
mergitur](https://example.com/): linguae. India
[errare](https://example.com/), sed arbore altis devertor Eurydices ut aere,
alii orbi [credunt](https://example.com) parenti mediumque inania
discedunt. Locus ullis postquam plangor defixa, nec sacris, forma! Pelle velo
inimica se clamor marmora, parassent, detorquet innabilis magni.

body.raw:
## Varas nota medios

Lorem markdownum rediit. Aevo ausus annis successit numen. Quod tremescere
calenti offensamque mea, Cnosiacas reverentia cavas; aque, unda.

Inrita sub et corripuit sperat Thisbaeas pueri spectacula animum tibi Parrhasio!
Puerique parant templi et e nec est diros et poma,
[Phrygia](https://example.com), ac has dementia est placuit. Cum
capax atque. Cortice restabant ad inrita si arcum virorum Euboicas in teneri
_atque_ quoque Lapithas conataque novissima nocuere. Non vituli, _sua venit eo_
rigidis clausus.

## Deae haec mecum concubitu vires mortalia scopulis

_Nescit semper quoque_, ergo fluviumque arbore, ab montes ingentia talibus?
Illum servanda iunctoque in an aethere deferre paene teloque. Ille Pallante
vidit, _et_ suprema?

Alis auras quem in caede tanta, flumina; ad ferarum ostendens tenus. Ceyx cum
inania, templis proelia terram favorem. Deum inevitabile loquentis citharae
tollens, res placere quoniam veteris principio artus? Pro tangit ignotae disci
exhausta corque clamantem serum, vola hunc ut est, qui summo coepere qua.
Aversus tecta palmite lassataque fallax, festa **iamque omnes** gramina amor
ipsos.

## Raras luna igni brevis et nuruumque viribus

Penthea soleo nullae! Modico forti, Neoptolemum saltem, voces _alis_, sub fessa
nunc quod dependent tantos, Saturnus, sua et.

> Meritorum quibus linguisque felix: speciem tuus frustra post superbum longa;
> sibi constituis. Nube Saturnius quaedam delphines Alcyone. Nobilis digitoque
> invita pronus sati vos, Di fuga! Avem vultus tantusque nimbisque capit hanc?

Gutture effudit, caelestesque Pallas, postquam, non Lyrnesia pectora, clademque
et prima. Mortali Procne desolatas, ad Iove vetat, et vita cucurri in nunc.
_Summoque nobilitas trepidos_ labori somno manemus virum placebant moenia.

## Varas nota medios

Lorem markdownum rediit. Aevo ausus annis successit numen. Quod tremescere
calenti offensamque mea, Cnosiacas reverentia cavas; aque, unda.

Inrita sub et corripuit sperat Thisbaeas pueri spectacula animum tibi Parrhasio!
Puerique parant templi et e nec est diros et poma,
[Phrygia](https://example.com), ac has dementia est placuit. Cum
capax atque. Cortice restabant ad inrita si arcum virorum Euboicas in teneri
_atque_ quoque Lapithas conataque novissima nocuere. Non vituli, _sua venit eo_
rigidis clausus.

## Deae haec mecum concubitu vires mortalia scopulis

_Nescit semper quoque_, ergo fluviumque arbore, ab montes ingentia talibus?
Illum servanda iunctoque in an aethere deferre paene teloque. Ille Pallante
vidit, _et_ suprema?

Alis auras quem in caede tanta, flumina; ad ferarum ostendens tenus. Ceyx cum
inania, templis proelia terram favorem. Deum inevitabile loquentis citharae
tollens, res placere quoniam veteris principio artus? Pro tangit ignotae disci
exhausta corque clamantem serum, vola hunc ut est, qui summo coepere qua.
Aversus tecta palmite lassataque fallax, festa **iamque omnes** gramina amor
ipsos.

## Raras luna igni brevis et nuruumque viribus

Penthea soleo nullae! Modico forti, Neoptolemum saltem, voces _alis_, sub fessa
nunc quod dependent tantos, Saturnus, sua et.

> Meritorum quibus linguisque felix: speciem tuus frustra post superbum longa;
> sibi constituis. Nube Saturnius quaedam delphines Alcyone. Nobilis digitoque
> invita pronus sati vos, Di fuga! Avem vultus tantusque nimbisque capit hanc?

Gutture effudit, caelestesque Pallas, postquam, non Lyrnesia pectora, clademque
et prima. Mortali Procne desolatas, ad Iove vetat, et vita cucurri in nunc.
_Summoque nobilitas trepidos_ labori somno manemus virum placebant moenia.

## Varas nota medios

Lorem markdownum rediit. Aevo ausus annis successit numen. Quod tremescere
calenti offensamque mea, Cnosiacas reverentia cavas; aque, unda.

Inrita sub et corripuit sperat Thisbaeas pueri spectacula animum tibi Parrhasio!
Puerique parant templi et e nec est diros et poma,
[Phrygia](https://example.com), ac has dementia est placuit. Cum
capax atque. Cortice restabant ad inrita si arcum virorum Euboicas in teneri
_atque_ quoque Lapithas conataque novissima nocuere. Non vituli, _sua venit eo_
rigidis clausus.

## Deae haec mecum concubitu vires mortalia scopulis

_Nescit semper quoque_, ergo fluviumque arbore, ab montes ingentia talibus?
Illum servanda iunctoque in an aethere deferre paene teloque. Ille Pallante
vidit, _et_ suprema?

Alis auras quem in caede tanta, flumina; ad ferarum ostendens tenus. Ceyx cum
inania, templis proelia terram favorem. Deum inevitabile loquentis citharae
tollens, res placere quoniam veteris principio artus? Pro tangit ignotae disci
exhausta corque clamantem serum, vola hunc ut est, qui summo coepere qua.
Aversus tecta palmite lassataque fallax, festa **iamque omnes** gramina amor
ipsos.

## Raras luna igni brevis et nuruumque viribus

Penthea soleo nullae! Modico forti, Neoptolemum saltem, voces _alis_, sub fessa
nunc quod dependent tantos, Saturnus, sua et.

> Meritorum quibus linguisque felix: speciem tuus frustra post superbum longa;

> invita pronus sati vos, Di fuga! Avem vultus tantusque nimbisque capit hanc?

Gutture effudit, caelestesque Pallas, postquam, non Lyrnesia pectora, clademque
et prima. Mortali Procne desolatas, ad Iove vetat, et vita cucurri in nunc.
_Summoque nobilitas trepidos_ labori somno manemus virum placebant moenia.

document.title: Effudit, caelestesque Palla sperat Thisbaeas pueri
document.description: Ipsum ullamco nisi cupidatat enim adipisicing esse consectetur eu.

body.raw:
## Varas nota medios

Lorem markdownum rediit. Aevo ausus annis successit numen. Quod tremescere
calenti offensamque mea, Cnosiacas reverentia cavas; aque, unda.

Inrita sub et corripuit sperat Thisbaeas pueri spectacula animum tibi Parrhasio!
Puerique parant templi et e nec est diros et poma,
[Phrygia](https://example.com), ac has dementia est placuit. Cum
capax atque. Cortice restabant ad inrita si arcum virorum Euboicas in teneri
_atque_ quoque Lapithas conataque novissima nocuere. Non vituli, _sua venit eo_
rigidis clausus.

## Deae haec mecum concubitu vires mortalia scopulis

_Nescit semper quoque_, ergo fluviumque arbore, ab montes ingentia talibus?
Illum servanda iunctoque in an aethere deferre paene teloque. Ille Pallante
vidit, _et_ suprema?

Alis auras quem in caede tanta, flumina; ad ferarum ostendens tenus. Ceyx cum
inania, templis proelia terram favorem. Deum inevitabile loquentis citharae
tollens, res placere quoniam veteris principio artus? Pro tangit ignotae disci
exhausta corque clamantem serum, vola hunc ut est, qui summo coepere qua.
Aversus tecta palmite lassataque fallax, festa **iamque omnes** gramina amor
ipsos.

## Raras luna igni brevis et nuruumque viribus

Penthea soleo nullae! Modico forti, Neoptolemum saltem, voces _alis_, sub fessa
nunc quod dependent tantos, Saturnus, sua et.

> Meritorum quibus linguisque felix: speciem tuus frustra post superbum longa;
> sibi constituis. Nube Saturnius quaedam delphines Alcyone. Nobilis digitoque
> invita pronus sati vos, Di fuga! Avem vultus tantusque nimbisque capit hanc?

Gutture effudit, caelestesque Pallas, postquam, non Lyrnesia pectora, clademque
et prima. Mortali Procne desolatas, ad Iove vetat, et vita cucurri in nunc.
_Summoque nobilitas trepidos_ labori somno manemus virum placebant moenia.

body.raw:
## Varas nota medios

Lorem markdownum rediit. Aevo ausus annis successit numen. Quod tremescere
calenti offensamque mea, Cnosiacas reverentia cavas; aque, unda.

Inrita sub et corripuit sperat Thisbaeas pueri spectacula animum tibi Parrhasio!
Puerique parant templi et e nec est diros et poma,
[Phrygia](https://example.com), ac has dementia est placuit. Cum
capax atque. Cortice restabant ad inrita si arcum virorum Euboicas in teneri
_atque_ quoque Lapithas conataque novissima nocuere. Non vituli, _sua venit eo_
rigidis clausus.

## Deae haec mecum concubitu vires mortalia scopulis

_Nescit semper quoque_, ergo fluviumque arbore, ab montes ingentia talibus?
Illum servanda iunctoque in an aethere deferre paene teloque. Ille Pallante
vidit, _et_ suprema?

Alis auras quem in caede tanta, flumina; ad ferarum ostendens tenus. Ceyx cum
inania, templis proelia terram favorem. Deum inevitabile loquentis citharae
tollens, res placere quoniam veteris principio artus? Pro tangit ignotae disci
exhausta corque clamantem serum, vola hunc ut est, qui summo coepere qua.
Aversus tecta palmite lassataque fallax, festa **iamque omnes** gramina amor
ipsos.

## Raras luna igni brevis et nuruumque viribus

Penthea soleo nullae! Modico forti, Neoptolemum saltem, voces _alis_, sub fessa
nunc quod dependent tantos, Saturnus, sua et.

> Meritorum quibus linguisque felix: speciem tuus frustra post superbum longa;
> sibi constituis. Nube Saturnius quaedam delphines Alcyone. Nobilis digitoque
> invita pronus sati vos, Di fuga! Avem vultus tantusque nimbisque capit hanc?

Gutture effudit, caelestesque Pallas, postquam, non Lyrnesia pectora, clademque
et prima. Mortali Procne desolatas, ad Iove vetat, et vita cucurri in nunc.
_Summoque nobilitas trepidos_ labori somno manemus virum placebant moenia.

body.raw:
## Varas nota medios

Lorem markdownum rediit. Aevo ausus annis successit numen. Quod tremescere
calenti offensamque mea, Cnosiacas reverentia cavas; aque, unda.

Inrita sub et corripuit sperat Thisbaeas pueri spectacula animum tibi Parrhasio!
Puerique parant templi et e nec est diros et poma,
[Phrygia](https://example.com), ac has dementia est placuit. Cum
capax atque. Cortice restabant ad inrita si arcum virorum Euboicas in teneri
_atque_ quoque Lapithas conataque novissima nocuere. Non vituli, _sua venit eo_
rigidis clausus.

## Deae haec mecum concubitu vires mortalia scopulis

_Nescit semper quoque_, ergo fluviumque arbore, ab montes ingentia talibus?
Illum servanda iunctoque in an aethere deferre paene teloque. Ille Pallante
vidit, _et_ suprema?

Alis auras quem in caede tanta, flumina; ad ferarum ostendens tenus. Ceyx cum
inania, templis proelia terram favorem. Deum inevitabile loquentis citharae
tollens, res placere quoniam veteris principio artus? Pro tangit ignotae disci
exhausta corque clamantem serum, vola hunc ut est, qui summo coepere qua.
Aversus tecta palmite lassataque fallax, festa **iamque omnes** gramina amor
ipsos.

## Raras luna igni brevis et nuruumque viribus

Penthea soleo nullae! Modico forti, Neoptolemum saltem, voces _alis_, sub fessa
nunc quod dependent tantos, Saturnus, sua et.

> Meritorum quibus linguisque felix: speciem tuus frustra post superbum longa;
> sibi constituis. Nube Saturnius quaedam delphines Alcyone. Nobilis digitoque
> invita pronus sati vos, Di fuga! Avem vultus tantusque nimbisque capit hanc?

Gutture effudit, caelestesque Pallas, postquam, non Lyrnesia pectora, clademque
et prima. Mortali Procne desolatas, ad Iove vetat, et vita cucurri in nunc.
_Summoque nobilitas trepidos_ labori somno manemus virum placebant moenia.

## Varas nota medios

Lorem markdownum rediit. Aevo ausus annis successit numen. Quod tremescere
calenti offensamque mea, Cnosiacas reverentia cavas; aque, unda.

Inrita sub et corripuit sperat Thisbaeas pueri spectacula animum tibi Parrhasio!
Puerique parant templi et e nec est diros et poma,
[Phrygia](https://example.com), ac has dementia est placuit. Cum
capax atque. Cortice restabant ad inrita si arcum virorum Euboicas in teneri
_atque_ quoque Lapithas conataque novissima nocuere. Non vituli, _sua venit eo_
rigidis clausus.

## Deae haec mecum concubitu vires mortalia scopulis

_Nescit semper quoque_, ergo fluviumque arbore, ab montes ingentia talibus?
Illum servanda iunctoque in an aethere deferre paene teloque. Ille Pallante
vidit, _et_ suprema?

Alis auras quem in caede tanta, flumina; ad ferarum ostendens tenus. Ceyx cum
inania, templis proelia terram favorem. Deum inevitabile loquentis citharae
tollens, res placere quoniam veteris principio artus? Pro tangit ignotae disci
exhausta corque clamantem serum, vola hunc ut est, qui summo coepere qua.
Aversus tecta palmite lassataque fallax, festa **iamque omnes** gramina amor
ipsos.

## Raras luna igni brevis et nuruumque viribus

Penthea soleo nullae! Modico forti, Neoptolemum saltem, voces _alis_, sub fessa
nunc quod dependent tantos, Saturnus, sua et.

> Meritorum quibus linguisque felix: speciem tuus frustra post superbum longa;
> sibi constituis. Nube Saturnius quaedam delphines Alcyone. Nobilis digitoque
> invita pronus sati vos, Di fuga! Avem vultus tantusque nimbisque capit hanc?

Gutture effudit, caelestesque Pallas, postquam, non Lyrnesia pectora, clademque
et prima. Mortali Procne desolatas, ad Iove vetat, et vita cucurri in nunc.
_Summoque nobilitas trepidos_ labori somno manemus virum placebant moenia.

## Varas nota medios

Lorem markdownum rediit. Aevo ausus annis successit numen. Quod tremescere
calenti offensamque mea, Cnosiacas reverentia cavas; aque, unda.

Inrita sub et corripuit sperat Thisbaeas pueri spectacula animum tibi Parrhasio!
Puerique parant templi et e nec est diros et poma,
[Phrygia](https://example.com), ac has dementia est placuit. Cum
capax atque. Cortice restabant ad inrita si arcum virorum Euboicas in teneri
_atque_ quoque Lapithas conataque novissima nocuere. Non vituli, _sua venit eo_
rigidis clausus.

## Deae haec mecum concubitu vires mortalia scopulis

_Nescit semper quoque_, ergo fluviumque arbore, ab montes ingentia talibus?
Illum servanda iunctoque in an aethere deferre paene teloque. Ille Pallante
vidit, _et_ suprema?

Alis auras quem in caede tanta, flumina; ad ferarum ostendens tenus. Ceyx cum
inania, templis proelia terram favorem. Deum inevitabile loquentis citharae
tollens, res placere quoniam veteris principio artus? Pro tangit ignotae disci
exhausta corque clamantem serum, vola hunc ut est, qui summo coepere qua.
Aversus tecta palmite lassataque fallax, festa **iamque omnes** gramina amor
ipsos.

## Raras luna igni brevis et nuruumque viribus

Penthea soleo nullae! Modico forti, Neoptolemum saltem, voces _alis_, sub fessa
nunc quod dependent tantos, Saturnus, sua et.

> Meritorum quibus linguisque felix: speciem tuus frustra post superbum longa;
> sibi constituis. Nube Saturnius quaedam delphines Alcyone. Nobilis digitoque
> invita pronus sati vos, Di fuga! Avem vultus tantusque nimbisque capit hanc?

Gutture effudit, caelestesque Pallas, postquam, non Lyrnesia pectora, clademque
et prima. Mortali Procne desolatas, ad Iove vetat, et vita cucurri in nunc.
_Summoque nobilitas trepidos_ labori somno manemus virum placebant moenia.

body.raw:
Blog is powered by [CMS](/docs/cms/overview) along with [Docs](/docs/cms/docs).

:::info
You can see a live example at [/blog](/blog)
:::

## How to write blog

See [CMS overview](/docs/cms/overview#how-to-write-blogdocs) for writing content in Markdown.

## Authors

You can define an author of blog posts in `/content/authors.ts`.

If `author` field in a blog post is undefined, `defaultAuthor` in [siteData](/docs/site-configuration#site-data-object) is used.

## Tags

Simply add `tags` field in the blog posts and all tags are automatically aggregated under `/blog/tags/[slug]` routes.

:::info
You don't need to pre-define tags somewhere else than posts' metadata.
:::

## Caveats

### Nested routes are not supported

All md/mdx files are expected to be placed at the **top level** of the `/content/blog` directory.

- DO - `/content/blog/post.mdx`
- DON'T - `/content/blog/category/post.mdx`

## What is Markdown?

Markdown is a way to style text on the web. You control the display of the document; formatting words as bold or italic, adding images, and creating lists are just a few of the things we can do with Markdown. Mostly, Markdown is just regular text with a few non-alphabetic characters thrown in, like `#` or `*`.

## Syntax guide

Here’s an overview of Markdown syntax that you can use anywhere on GitHub.com or in your own text files.

### Headings

```txt
## This is a h2 tag

### This is a h3 tag

#### This is a h4 tag
```

## This is a h2 tag

### This is a h3 tag

#### This is a h4 tag

:::info
h2 should be the top-level heading instead of h1 which is for the title.
:::

### Emphasis

```txt
_This text will be italic_

**This text will be bold**

_You **can** combine them_
```

_This text will be italic_

**This text will be bold**

_You **can** combine them_

### Strikethrough

Any word wrapped with two tildes (like `~~this~~`) will appear ~~crossed out~~.

### Lists

#### Unordered

```txt
- Item 1
- Item 2
  - Item 2a
  - Item 2b
```

- Item 1
- Item 2
  - Item 2a
  - Item 2b

#### Ordered

```txt
1. Item 1
1. Item 2
1. Item 3
   1. Item 3a
   1. Item 3b
```

1. Item 1
1. Item 2
1. Item 3
   1. Item 3a
   1. Item 3b

### Images

```txt
![Office](/images/office-chairs.webp)
```

![Office](/images/office-chairs.webp)

### Links

```txt
http://github.com

[GitHub](http://github.com)
```

http://github.com

[GitHub](http://github.com)

### Blockquotes

```txt
As Kanye West said:

> We're living the future so
> the present is our past.
```

As Kanye West said:

> We're living the future so
> the present is our past.

### Inline code

```txt
I think you should use an `<addr>` element here instead.
```

I think you should use an `<addr>` element here instead.

### Syntax highlighting

Here’s an example of how you can use syntax highlighting with [GitHub Flavored Markdown](https://help.github.com/articles/basic-writing-and-formatting-syntax/):

````txt
```js title="/lib/sum.js"
// Some comments
function sum(x, y) {
  return x + y;
}
```
````

And here's how it looks - nicely colored with styled code titles!

```js title="/lib/sum.js"
// Some comments
function sum(x, y) {
  return x + y;
}
```

### Messages

```txt
:::info
You can use **Markdown** inside `Message`.
:::

:::warn
You can use **Markdown** inside `Message`.
:::

:::danger
You can use **Markdown** inside `Message`.
:::
```

:::info
You can use **Markdown** inside `Message`.
:::

:::warn
You can use **Markdown** inside `Message`.
:::

:::danger
You can use **Markdown** inside `Message`.
:::

### Tables

You can create tables by assembling a list of words and dividing them with hyphens `-` (for the first row), and then separating each column with a pipe `|`:

```txt
| First Header                | Second Header                |
| --------------------------- | ---------------------------- |
| Content from cell 1         | Content from cell 2          |
| Content in the first column | Content in the second column |
```

| First Header                | Second Header                |
| --------------------------- | ---------------------------- |
| Content from cell 1         | Content from cell 2          |
| Content in the first column | Content in the second column |

body.raw:
## Next App

[Vercel](https://vercel.com) is the easiest hosting service for Next.js apps (Next.js is built by them).

## Static export

As files generated by `next export` are just static assets, it should work on any hosting service.

Here are some hosting services that offer free/cheap plans for static sites:

- [Vercel](https://vercel.com)
- [Netlify](https://www.netlify.com/)
- [Cloudflare Pages](https://pages.cloudflare.com/)
- [GitHub Pages](https://pages.github.com/)
- [Firebase Hosting](https://firebase.google.com/)
- [AWS S3](https://aws.amazon.com/s3/?nc1=h_ls)

body.raw:
## Prerequisites

- Basic knowledge of Git, Node, TypeScript, React, Next.js.
- Git, Node and pnpm are installed.

## Start development

Run the following command to install the dependencies required by all sub-packages:

```bash
pnpm install
```

Then:

```bash
pnpm dev
```

And open `localhost:3930` in your browser and the Next app should be running.

## Build for production

```bash
pnpm build
```

## Lint and check types

```bash
pnpm lint
pnpm format
pnpm typecheck
```

body.raw:
## What is Saazy Template?

Saazy Template is a repository that contains a Next.js app and reusable components for building a beautiful marketing website for SaaS or anything else.

## Highlights

- 12+ beautifully designed pages.
- Fully responsive.
- [Contentlayer](https://www.contentlayer.dev/) based CMS – write **blog** and **docs** with type-safe Markdown/MDX.
- Powered by [Camome UI](https://camome.net).
- Dark mode supported.
- Basic SEO.
- Free updates.

## What are included?

### Pages

- [Home](/)
- [Contact](/contact)
- [Pricing](/pricing)
- [Form submission](/success)
- [Sign in](/signin)
- [Sign up](/signup)
- [MDX page](/mdx-page)
- [404](/404)
- Blog
  - [All posts](/blog)
  - [Single post](/blog/example)
  - [Tag](/blog/tags/example-tag)
- [Docs](/docs/develop/introduction) (we are here)

### Blog/Docs

See [CMS](/docs/cms/overview) to know how the content management system works.

See [Blog](/docs/cms/blog) and [Docs](/docs/cms/docs) for details about each feature.

### Forms

Saazy has built-in form features enabled out of the box.

## Tech stacks

- [TypeScript](https://www.typescriptlang.org/) for most code.
- [Next.js](https://nextjs.org/) for framework, **OR** static HTML/CSS/JavaScript.
- [Camome UI](https://camome.net) for UI framework.
- [CSS Modules](https://github.com/css-modules/css-modules) for styling.
- [Contentlayer](https://www.contentlayer.dev/) for processing markdown/mdx files for blog and docs.
- [heroicons](https://heroicons.com/) for most of the icons.
- [pnpm](https://pnpm.io) for package manager.
- [ESLint](https://eslint.org/) for linter.
- [Prettier](https://prettier.io/) for formatter.

body.raw:
## `siteData` object

You can customize your site's metadata in `/content/siteData.ts`.

```ts title="/content/siteData.ts"
const url = "https://saazy.camome.net";
const siteData = {
  title: "Saazy",
  subTitle: "Grow your business with your customers",
  description: "This is description text about your website.",
  url,
  ogImage: url + "/images/og.png",
  defaultAuthor: "john-doe",
  defaultBlogPostImg: "/images/post-placeholder.webp",
  blogPostsPerPage: 9,
};
```

## OG image

Just replace `/public/images/og.png` or modify `/src/components/DefaultSeo.tsx` for more precise control.

## Favicon

Generate favicons from single file by [Faviconize](https://github.com/sabigara/faviconize), a Deno CLI tool I developed.

```bash
deno run --unstable --allow-read --allow-write --allow-ffi \
 "https://deno.land/x/faviconize/cmd.ts" \
 -i "path/to/icon.<svg or png>" \
 -o "path/to/outdir/"
```

:::warn
You need Deno runtime installed in you machine.
:::

body.raw:
## What do "free updates" include?

Once you purchase our product, any improvements listed below will always be free:

- Feature improvements
- Bug fixes
- Upgrade of dependencies

Updates are applied to the download content on [Lemon Squeezy](https://lemonsqueezy.com). You are responsive for downloading, merging the changes into your code base, and ensuring no regression is introduced.

## What kind of support do you provide?

While we do offer support for things like licensing-related concerns, customers are expected to have the requisite knowledge of HTML, CSS, JavaScript, React and Next.js to use the product successfully.

However, in case you face a serious bug, please file an issue to our [GitHub community](https://github.com/camomeui/camome).

**In short:**

- We **DO** fix serious bugs introduced by ourselves
- We **DON'T** offer support for questions about how to use our products

## What browsers are supported?

We support the latest version of Chrome, Firefox, and Safari.

Internet Explorer is not supported.

## What versions of dependencies are used?

| Dependency | Version |
| ---------- | ------- |
| TypeScript | ^4.9    |
| Next.js    | ^13     |
| React      | ^18     |

## Still have questions?

[Email me](mailto:lemonburst1958@gmail.com).

What versions of dependencies are used?

body.raw:
## Overview

The license grants permission to an individual or entity (the Licensee) to access and use the Product.

You **can**:

- Use the Products to create unlimited End Products.
- Use the Products to create unlimited End Products for unlimited Clients.
- Use the Products to create End Products where the End Product is sold to End Users.
- Use the Products to create End Products that are open source and freely available to End Users.

You **cannot**:

- Use the Products to create End Products that are designed to allow an End User to build their own End Products using the Products or derivatives of the Products.
- Re-distribute the Products or derivatives of the Products separately from an End Product, neither in code nor as design assets.

## Terminology

**Licensee** is the individual or entity who has purchased a license.

**Products** are the source code and design assets made available to the Licensee after purchasing a license.

**End Product** is any artifact produced that incorporates the Products or derivatives of the Products.

**End User** is a user of an End Product.

**Client** is an individual or entity receiving custom professional services directly from the Licensee, produced specifically for that individual or entity.
